# E-Joy Global Workflow

- Work in small tasks (2-4 hours) with clear acceptance criteria.
- Keep `main` releasable; use `feature/*` branches and merge via PR.
- Before finishing any task, run: lint, type-check, test, build.
- Prefer existing project patterns over introducing new abstractions.
- Do not use `latest` image tags or unpinned runtime versions.
- Keep commit messages conventional (feat/fix/refactor/docs/test/chore).
- For UI work, define IA (information architecture) and AC (acceptance criteria) first; do not code without them.
- Any role-specific module must have explicit mode boundaries (customer vs admin vs system-admin); no implicit UI reuse.
- If task includes demo/start scripts, verify runtime prerequisites (Node/pnpm/version/ports) before claiming done.

## Done Criteria (every task)

- Code implemented and reviewed.
- Tests added/updated for behavior change.
- Docs updated when API/flow changed.
- CI-ready locally (all key checks pass).
- For UI tasks: loading/empty/error/permission-denied states are implemented and manually checked.
